{"key":"processedPost-12690091","value":{"id":12690091,"first":12689260,"last":12691255,"when":1275742989,"utime":"06/05/10 04:03 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />The substrate seems to be drying out and pulling away from the trays<br /></blockquote><br /><br />That's not from drying out.&nbsp; As the mycelium consumes the substrate as food, the substrate naturally gets smaller.&nbsp; You should line the aluminum tray with black plastic before filling, so that as the substrate shrinks, the plastic remains attached to it, preventing the gap.&nbsp; It will also prevent the mycelium from digesting the aluminum, destroying it.<br /><br />That aside, if the only place you're seeing pinning is in the gap around the edges, your humidity is too low.<br />RR","title":"Re: Disapointing pinset.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}